                        <h4 class="text-white">Gin</h4>
                    </section>
                    <section class="card-body text-center">
                        <p><strong>What: </strong>Gin is a neutral grain spirit, typically triple distilled and cut with
                            distilled water. On the final distilation botanicals are introduced, most famously juniper.
                            But there are other staples as well such as coriander, orange peel, lemon peel, anise,
                            cassia caraway and many others.</p>
                        <p><strong>Where: </strong>There are three approximate types of gin that tend to come from
                            certain places. <strong>London Dry Gin, Genever/Hollands, and Plymouth Gin</strong></p>
                    </section>
                </section>

            </section>

