                        <h4 class="text-white">Vodka</h4>
                    </section>
                    <section class="card-body text-center">
                        <p><strong>What: </strong>Vodka is a distillate that has been distilled to such a high proof,
                            that very few oil, aromas or flavors remain. Generaly Vodka is distilled to higher than 95
                            percent alcohol by volume and then filtered.</p>
                        <p><strong>Where: </strong>Russia and Poland are the most renowned and historically imporant
                            early producers of Vodka in large volumes. The filtration techniqes created by these
                            contries has a great influence on the worlds other Vodka producers.</p>
                    </section>
                </section>

