                <section class="card mt-3 mb-3">
                    <section class="card-header text-center header-background-rum">
                        <h4 class="text-white">Rum</h4>
                    </section>
                    <section class="card-body text-center">
                        <p><strong>What: </strong>Rum is any distilled spirit created from sugarcane. The majority of rums are produced from molasses, the by-product of refining sugarcane into raw sugar. Molassas is used to make light soft rums to dark, pungent rums and anything in between</p>
                        <p><strong>Where: </strong>Rum can be made anywhere sugarcane can be grown or exported to. Over two hundred years ago, most of the rum produced was made in England, as they imported most of the molasses produced in the Caribean.</p>
                    </section>
                </section>

            </section>

