                        <h4 class="text-white">Cachaca</h4>
                    </section>
                    <section class="card-body text-center">
                        <p><strong>What: </strong>Cachaca, like Rum, is distilled from sugarcae. The difference is what part. Cachaca is produced from the juice of the sugarcane after it's pressed.</p>
                        <p><strong>Where: </strong>Cachaca can only be produced in Brazil. Incredible, 98 percent of all cachaca is consumed in Brazil. Cachaca comes in three classifications: unaged (1 year in wood), aged (2 to 12 years in wood), and yellow(unaged spirits that have caramel or wood extracts added to appear older)</p>
                    </section>
                </section>

