                    </section>
                    <section class="card-body text-center">
                        <p><strong>What: </strong>Tequila is a distilled spirit made from the agave plant. First the Agave Hearts are either baked in ovens or steamed in autoclaves (baked is better), and shredded, then the juice of the hearts is pressed out fermented and distilled. Most of the best Tequila is distilled in pot stills or small hybrid stills.</p>
                        <p><strong>Where: </strong>Tequila is a term tightly defined and controlled by the Mexican govenrment. Most major contries honor and protect these regulations and defentions, expect for the United States. Tequila is produced in the five Mexican states, Jalisco, Nayarit, Gunajato, Michoacan and Tamaulipas.</p>
                    </section>
                </section>

