                        <h4 class="text-white">Mezcal</h4>
                    </section>
                    <section class="card-body text-center">
                        <p><strong>What: </strong>Mezcal, like Tequila, is distilled from the Agave heart juice. The differece is how. To make Mezcal, the Agave Hearts are cooked in a pit underground with hot rocks and Agave Fronds for days or even weeks. And the resulting juice is distilled in ancient clay pot stills. Resulting in a smoky and earthy spirit.</p>
                        <p><strong>Where: </strong>Mezcal, lilke Tequila, is a term tightly defined and controlled by the Mexican govenrment. Mezcal is primarily made in Oaxaca, Mexico, But seven other states also earned a Denomination of Origin:Guerrero, Durango, San Luis Potos√≠, Zacatecas, Guanajuato, Tamaulipas and Michoacan.</p>
