                    <section class="card-body text-center">
                        <p><strong>What: </strong>Brandy is generaly an aged grape spirit made from distilled wine that has been aged in oak for a specific amoutn of time, Usually six months or longer. There are some exemptions, such as Calvados, which is made from Apples and Pears.</p>
                        <p><strong>Where: </strong>Brandy can be made anywhere you can wine and distle it. Although there are some kinds of Brandy that have to be made in a specific region with a specifc juice. Some of these Brandy's include <strong>Cognac: </strong>Cognac has to be made form Ugni Blanc grapes and aged in Limousin Oak barrels for at leasst two years. These Grapes must also be gorwn in Cognac France.<strong>Pisco: </strong>Pisco is made from gapes in either Chile or Peru. Each country ahs its own set of grapes from which they ferment wine and distill Pisco.</p>
